    <etym xml:lang="ru">Восходит к <mentioned xml:lang="ira"><lang/><w>*band-</w></mentioned> с
        ассимиляцией %ind%i → %idd%i → %itt%i (как <ref type="xr" target="#entry_sæddyn"/> ‘ломать’
        из *%isændyn%i, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_æddæ"/> ‘вне’ из %iændæ%i). Существование в
        прошлом формы *%ibændyn%i не вызывает сомнения; она отложилась в <ref type="xr"
            target="#entry_bændæn"/> ‘веревка’, в <ref type="xr" target="#entry_nyvændyn"/> (из
        *%iny-bændyn%i ← %ini%i-%iband%i-) ‘наматывать пряжу для тканья’, <ref type="xr"
            target="#entry_ivændun"/> (← *%ivi%i-%iband%i-) id. Основа %iband%i- ‘вязать’ с ее
        разновидностями имеет общеиндоевропейское распространение: <mentioned xml:lang="fa"
                ><lang/><w>band-: bast-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="pal"><lang/><w>band-:
                bast-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="x-balochi"><lang/><w>bandag :
            bast-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ku"><lang/><w>band-: bast-</w></mentioned>,
            <mentioned xml:lang="wbl"><lang/><w>vand- : vast-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned
            xml:lang="yah"><lang/><w>vand- : vəst-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sgh"
                ><lang/><w>vīnd-: vūst-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="yai"
                ><lang/><w>vant-</w></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="yai"><w>vand-</w></mentioned>,
        , <mentioned xml:lang="sog"><lang/><w>*βand-(βnt-)</w></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="sog"
                ><w>*βandak-(βntk-)</w><gloss><q>раб</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
            xml:lang="sog"><w>*βast-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sog"><w>*βastak(βst-,
                βstk)</w><gloss><q>связанный</q></gloss></mentioned>, , <mentioned xml:lang="zkh"
                ><lang/><w>βancin</w><gloss><q>я привязал</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
            xml:lang="kho"><lang/><w>bad-: basta-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ae"
                ><lang/><w>bañd-: basta-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="peo"
                ><lang/><w>ba(n)daka</w><gloss><q>слуга</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
            xml:lang="sa"><lang/><w>bandh-: basta-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"
                ><lang/><w>badhnāti</w><gloss><q>он вяжет</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
            xml:lang="txh"><lang/><w>βενδ-</w></mentioned>
                (<bibl><author>Kretschmer</author><biblScope>Einleitung in die Geschichte der
                griechischen Sprache, стр. 236</biblScope></bibl>), <mentioned xml:lang="got"
                ><lang/><w>bindan</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="de"><lang/><w>binden:
                band</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="de"
                    ><lang/><w>Band</w><gloss><q>перевязь</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
            xml:lang="en"><lang/><w>bind: bound</w></mentioned> и пр. Ср. <ref type="xr"
            target="#entry_særbæddæn"/>. Причастие %ibast%i лексикализовалось в значении ‘сверток’,
        ‘связка’; ср. <mentioned xml:lang="kho"><lang/><w>basta</w></mentioned>, <mentioned
            xml:lang="sog"><lang/><w>*βast</w></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="sog"
            ><w>*βastak</w></mentioned>, и др.%n<bibl><ref target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._ОЭ"
                /><biblScope>II 47 сл.</biblScope></bibl>; <bibl><ref target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._Gr."
                /><biblScope>63</biblScope></bibl>.— <bibl><ref target="#ref_Hübschmann._Oss."
                /><biblScope>28</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl><ref target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"/><biblScope>23,
                26</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
    <etym xml:lang="en">It traces back to <mentioned xml:lang="ira"><lang/><w>*band-</w></mentioned>
        with the follwoing assimilation: %ind%i → %idd%i → %itt%i (like <ref type="xr"
            target="#entry_sæddyn"/> ‘break’ from *%isændyn%i, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_æddæ"/>
        ‘outside’ from %iændæ%i). The form *%ibændyn%i which existed in the past is beyond doubt; it
        is found in <ref type="xr" target="#entry_bændæn"/> ‘rope’, in <ref type="xr"
            target="#entry_nyvændyn"/> (from *%iny-bændyn%i ← %ini%i-%iband%i-) ‘wind yarn for
        weaving’, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_ivændun"/> (← *%ivi%i-%iband%i-) id. The stem
        %iband%i- ‘bind’ with its variations is common in Indo-European languages: <mentioned
            xml:lang="fa"><lang/><w>band-: bast-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="pal"
                ><lang/><w>band-: bast-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="x-balochi"
                ><lang/><w>bandag : bast-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ku"><lang/><w>band-:
                bast-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="wbl"><lang/><w>vand- :
            vast-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="yah"><lang/><w>vand- :
        vəst-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sgh"><lang/><w>vīnd-: vūst-</w></mentioned>,
            <mentioned xml:lang="yai"><lang/><w>vant-</w></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="yai"
                ><w>vand-</w></mentioned>, , <mentioned xml:lang="sog"
            ><lang/><w>*βand-(βnt-)</w></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="sog"
                    ><w>*βandak-(βntk-)</w><gloss><q>slave</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
            xml:lang="sog"><w>*βast-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sog"><w>*βastak(βst-,
                βstk)</w><gloss><q>bound</q></gloss></mentioned>, , <mentioned xml:lang="zkh"
                ><lang/><w>βancin</w><gloss><q>I bound</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
            xml:lang="kho"><lang/><w>bad-: basta-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ae"
                ><lang/><w>bañd-: basta-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="peo"
                ><lang/><w>ba(n)daka</w><gloss><q>servant</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
            xml:lang="sa"><lang/><w>bandh-: basta-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"
                ><lang/><w>badhnāti</w><gloss><q>he binds</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
            xml:lang="txh"><lang/><w>βενδ-</w></mentioned>
                (<bibl><author>Kretschmer</author><biblScope>Einleitung in die Geschichte der
                griechischen Sprache, p. 236</biblScope></bibl>), <mentioned xml:lang="got"
                ><lang/><w>bindan</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="de"><lang/><w>binden:
                band</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="de"
                ><lang/><w>Band</w><gloss><q>sling</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="en"
                ><lang/><w>bind: bound</w></mentioned> etc. Cf. <ref type="xr"
            target="#entry_særbæddæn"/>. The participle %ibast%i was lexicalized with the meaning
        ‘roll’, ‘bunch’; cf. <mentioned xml:lang="kho"><lang/><w>basta</w></mentioned>, <mentioned
            xml:lang="sog"><lang/><w>*βast</w></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="sog"
            ><w>*βastak</w></mentioned>, etc.%n<bibl><ref target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._ОЭ"
                /><biblScope>II 47f.</biblScope></bibl>; <bibl><ref target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._Gr."
                /><biblScope>63</biblScope></bibl>.— <bibl><ref target="#ref_Hübschmann._Oss."
                /><biblScope>28</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl><ref target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"/><biblScope>23,
                26</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
